@FeralSmurf if you tried my snippet could you  check and see what your install directory looks like? You should have a `Boltgun/Content/Movies` and a `Boltgun/Content/Movies.old` folder both with the same set of mp4 files in there.

And if you compare the output of `ffmpeg -i Boltgun/Content/Movies/BoltgunCutscenes_C1Intro.mp4` to the one I posted above then you should see that there are 2 streams (1 video h264, 1 audio aac) instead of the 3 from the original.

If you want to undo it you can delete `Boltgun/Content/Movies` and rename `Boltgun/Content/Movies.old` back to `Boltgun/Content/Movies`.

@alasky17 I've experienced this issue with various versions of SteamOS and Bazzite. Usually I have no keyboard connected, only the Xbox 360 USB dongle for wireless gamepads and sometimes a couple of BT gamepads.

It doesn't seem to be 100% deterministic to me (but close): At one family gathering (before learning about the SteamDeck=0 fix) we kept rebooting the Deck and our controllers many many times, and sometimes the game worked. I've also run into a variation of this bug on Windows once, but there it seems to be the absolute exception.

I love this game to death, especially its coop mode. If there is anything I can do to debug this, please let me know.

